&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience in Product Management, with proven leadership managing cross-cultural, geographically distributed teams - operating at similar level (Director)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of enterprise SaaS such as CRM, Analytics, Billing &amp;amp; Rating systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with back-office systems such as:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong strategic thinking, business acumen, and the ability to influence through data and presentations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in managing global, enterprise-scale cloud services, including technical, security, and regulatory aspects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience delivering complex projects or business transformations in the BSS and OSS areas due to acquisitions, strong growth and digital transformations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with security, scalability and best practices around high-volume transactions use-cases, especially with API Gateways, Identity Management and Data analytics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous software development experience at some point in your career (strongly preferred) or as a minimum well versed in using SQL, Kibana and understanding complex data models in detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptable, with a growth mindset and a track record of success in startups or large enterprises&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
